The paper focuses on understanding search queries, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of a knowledge base (KB) suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The proposed methods involve machine learning, which is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
